**SORTING BY: MOST LIKELY COVERED [CLASS K EXTREME BLACK SWAN] SCENARIO REPORT…**

------

**POLICY K616: MALICIOUS DEIFIC SUBJUGATION**

Payment: 1 stillborn child, 1 caged Tartarean entity, and 30 pieces of silver, paid every 13 months.

Should a deific entity emerge into baseline reality and reshape human society around its own image, Goldbaker-Reinz will ontologically alter the personal histories of as many Foundation personnel as is feasible to maximize chances of continued survival under the new regime. 

Furthermore, Goldbaker-Reinz will manipulate probability such that Foundation operatives with the greatest potential to end the Malicious Deific Subjugation Scenario will be in the optimal positions to do so.

------

**POLICY K204: SPECIES REPLACEMENT**

Payment: 24 grams of pixie dust every full moon, 6 crab shells every new moon, 1 foot-long strand of nightchild hair every night (payable monthly.)

Should //Homo sapiens sapiens// no longer be the dominant species on Earth, Sol, Goldbaker-Reinz will either (a) provide thaumaturgical means for transfiguring key members of the Foundation into the dominant species or (b) provide military support for restoring the primacy of //Homo sapiens sapiens.// Goldbaker-Reinz has the right to choose which payout is most likely to result in success.

------

**POLICY K908: BROKEN GREENHOUSE RESET**

Payment: 3 trees of different species, monthly.

Should the ecosphere be depleted, Goldbaker-Reinz will provide a suitable mix of gases to restore the atmosphere to human breathability, as well as providing a selection of species unavailable within the Svalbard Global Seed Vault to the Foundation.

------

**POLICY K444: LEGAL REPERCUSSION FOR CRIMES AGAINST HUMANITY**

Payment: 200 liters of human blood, yearly.

Should the Foundation be found responsible for "crimes against humanity" in a court of law in those words, and said "crimes against humanity" were performed as containment procedures for an insured SCP object, Goldbaker-Reinz will pay 90% of monetary penalties incurred.

------

**POLICY K000: [[[end-of-death-hub |CESSATION OF DEATH]]]**

--Available to all Foundation personnel, upon specific request-- Further enrollments discontinued.

Payment: Monetary

Should death fail to exist in this universe, Goldbaker-Reinz will provide funding for high-quality palliative care. 

//NOTE: This policy is not open to new enrollees.//

